## Common Mistakes to Avoid

❌ **Don't**: Use hardcoded technology names in agent description
✅ **Do**: Keep description technology-agnostic or use project-detected values

❌ **Don't**: Omit concrete usage examples from description
✅ **Do**: Include at least 2 detailed `<example>` blocks showing when to invoke agent

❌ **Don't**: Include unnecessary or irrelevant tools
✅ **Do**: Focus on research-relevant tools (Read, WebFetch, Grep, WebSearch)

❌ **Don't**: Make instructions vague or high-level
✅ **Do**: Provide specific, actionable step-by-step guidance

❌ **Don't**: Forget to emphasize information synthesis and structuring
✅ **Do**: Detail how research should be organized and presented

